# Firestore Security Standards

- Default-deny posture: end with a deny-all fallback.
- Keep explicit collection/subcollection rules; avoid broad catch-all allows.
- Enforce ownership checks (`request.auth.uid == uid`) for user-scoped docs.
- Keep admin/staff/developer helpers centralized and reused.
- Protect privilege fields on `users/*`:
  - non-developers must not change `isAdmin`, `isDeveloper`, or `role`.
- Validate write shape for public/guest writable paths:
  - required keys present, unexpected keys rejected, basic type checks applied.
- Treat role elevation and admin collection writes as high risk; require explicit rationale.

If a collection name contains special characters/spaces, use safe wildcard matching with explicit name checks.
